<h2>Beastmaster Ranger</h2>

<p><strong>Class:</strong> Ranger (Beast Master) / Cleric (War Domain)</p>
<p><strong>Race:</strong> Any (recommended: Drow Half‑Elf for flavor)</p>
<p><strong>Background:</strong> Haunted One (for Act 1 cloak)</p>

<h3>Stats</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Strength:</strong> 8</li>
    <li><strong>Dexterity:</strong> 16 (14 + 2)</li>
    <li><strong>Constitution:</strong> 16 (15 + 1)</li>
    <li><strong>Intelligence:</strong> 10</li>
    <li><strong>Wisdom:</strong> 14</li>
    <li><strong>Charisma:</strong> 10</li>
</ul>

<h3>Build Summary</h3>
<p>
    This build brings you to the frontline as a melee‑focused Beast Master Ranger. You fight alongside your animal companion as a bruiser who controls the battlefield, blinds enemies, and applies pressure while staying durable. With strong AC, powerful pets, and consistent damage, this build shines in every act.
</p>

<h3>Character Progression</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Level 1 — Ranger:</strong> Favoured Enemy: Ranger Knight. Natural Explorer: Wasteland Wanderer (Fire) or Beast Tamer. Frontline stats with Dex focus.</li>
    <li><strong>Level 2 — Ranger:</strong> Spells: Hunter’s Mark, Ensnaring Strike. Fighting Style: Defense (recommended).</li>
    <li><strong>Level 3 — Ranger:</strong> Subclass: Beast Master. Companion: Raven or Bear early. Spells: Longstrider or Hail of Thorns.</li>
    <li><strong>Level 4 — Ranger:</strong> Feat: Alert (go first, never surprised).</li>
    <li><strong>Level 5 — Ranger:</strong> Extra Attack. Companion’s Bond (huge AC & damage boost). Spell: Pass Without Trace.</li>
    <li><strong>Level 6 — Ranger:</strong> Favoured Enemy: Bounty Hunter. Natural Explorer: Wasteland Wanderer (Cold).</li>
    <li><strong>Level 7 — Ranger:</strong> Exceptional Training (companion bonus actions). Spell: Spike Growth.</li>
    <li><strong>Level 8 — Ranger:</strong> Land’s Stride. Feat: Ability Improvement or Alert.</li>
    <li><strong>Level 9 — Ranger:</strong> Spell: Conjure Barrage (fun AoE, scales with weapon damage).</li>
    <li><strong>Level 10 — Ranger:</strong> Hide in Plain Sight (+10 Stealth, invisibility while still). Favoured Enemy: Mage Breaker. Natural Explorer: Wasteland Wanderer (Poison).</li>
    <li><strong>Level 11 — Ranger:</strong> Bestial Fury (companion Extra Attack — massive power spike). Spell: Lightning Arrow.</li>
    <li><strong>Level 12 — Cleric (War Domain):</strong> Bonus action attacks via War Priest. Spells: Create Water, Command, Healing Word, Sanctuary.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Key Spells</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Hunter’s Mark:</strong> Core damage engine.</li>
    <li><strong>Ensnaring Strike:</strong> Lock enemies down.</li>
    <li><strong>Pass Without Trace:</strong> +10 Stealth for the whole party.</li>
    <li><strong>Spike Growth:</strong> Area control.</li>
    <li><strong>Lightning Arrow:</strong> Burst damage.</li>
    <li><strong>War Domain Spells:</strong> Sanctuary, Healing Word, Command.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Equipment (Endgame)</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Helmet:</strong> Circlet of Hunting — +1d4 to attack rolls vs marked or revealed targets.</li>
    <li><strong>Cloak:</strong> Cloak of Protection — +1 AC.</li>
    <li><strong>Armor:</strong> Armour of Agility — full Dex to AC, +2 saves.</li>
    <li><strong>Ring 1:</strong> Eversight Ring — immunity to blindness.</li>
    <li><strong>Ring 2:</strong> Shadow‑Cloaked Ring — +1d4 damage in dim/heavy obscurity.</li>
    <li><strong>Boots:</strong> Evasive Shoes — +1 AC.</li>
    <li><strong>Weapon:</strong> Phalar Aluve — strong weapon actions.</li>
    <li><strong>Shield:</strong> Viconia’s Walking Fortress — +3 AC, reflect projectiles, knockdown chance, Warding Bond.</li>
    <li><strong>Gloves:</strong> Craterflesh Gloves — +1d6 force on crits (or Helldusk Gloves for fire).</li>
    <li><strong>Amulet:</strong> Amulet of Greater Health — sets Constitution to 23.</li>
    <li><strong>Ranged Weapon:</strong> Hellrider Bow — initiative bonus and debuff on hit.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Playstyle Tips</h3>
<p>
    You are a frontline bruiser supported by a powerful animal companion. Use Hunter’s Mark early, control space with Spike Growth, and let your pet blind, tank, or pressure enemies. With high AC, strong utility, and consistent damage, you can dance through the battlefield while your companion tears foes apart.
</p>
<p>
    Have fun with this build as you blaze through the game!
</p>